==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emblematize
<hw>Em*blem"a*tize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Emblematized</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Emblematizing</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To represent by, or as by, an emblem; to
symbolize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Anciently the sun was commonly <qex>emblematized</qex> by a starry
or radiate figure.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hurd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emblement</ent>⟦br⟧
